National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan recently held a discussion with his counterparts from the five Nordic countries to discuss ways to strengthen Transatlantic security. The main focus of the conversation was on potential measures to be taken against Russia if it continues to show aggression towards Ukraine. The importance of diplomatic efforts, such as the Strategic Stability Dialogue, NATO-Russia Council, and OSCE, in de-escalating the situation was emphasized. The participants also expressed their commitment to Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity. Sullivan praised the Nordic countries for their dedication to the values and principles that support European security. The countries involved in the call were Denmark, Finland, Iceland, Norway, and Sweden.